9. Set the concurrent connection to a value of around 5, i think it gives the best accuracy/speed ratio

10. Look for 'Status 302' in the Turbo Intruder table. If found, in its HTTP response is a parameter 'session=<value>' which is a session's cookie

11. If there is no 'Status 302' start the script once again, sometimes the Turbo Intruder omits some requests (e.g. the code was 0382 but the requests were sent too fast and request with the 0382 code was not received
by the server)

12. Copy the <value> of the 'session' and go back to the Burpsuite browser. Right click on the labs website and select Inspect -> Application
Now in the Application tab look for the Cookies tab. Under Cookies tab there should be a sub tab with the lab URL
Double click it and a new table with sessions will open. Double click on any of the sessions' cookies and replace with the <value> you copied instead 
Refresh the page, click on my account and it is solved
